deck_excerpt: Turn 1 Complete lockdown: Opponent cannot activate spells, traps, or monster effects.
deck_description: Most underrated thing I've ever seen. Will explain how it works if asked but after reading each card and playing around with it its self evident.  Board Possibilities:  1) Simorgh Link, Apex Avian, Barrier Statute, Harpie's feather storm (extra simorgh monster to protect link if possible)  2) Simorgh Link, Dark Simorgh, Anti-Spell Fragrance, Harpie's feather storm (extra simorgh monster to protect link if possible)  Any mix of the above can be made if you have the extenders. Use the Simorgh spells to extra-normal summon Avian without tributing if you have it in your hand. You can also end on the other two big simorgh birds but they aren't as good. If you manage to get traptrick or harpie's feather storm in conjuction with either/both of dark simorgh+spell fragrance or avian+barrier statute, or both, your opponent will quit.  Only weakness if evenly matched. Save Apex Avian or Simorgh of Darkness's effect(s) for this. Link Simorgh makes them all immune to infinite impermanence, so for the most part traps that can be played directly from the hand aren't a threat despite normally being capable or circumventing the simorgh lock.

deck_excerpt: Powerful beasts that will destroy your opponents!
deck_description: Thought Id come back and revisit this deck. Haven't really played Yu-Gi-Oh in a while, but this little patch should clear up a good part of the deck clutter that I experienced with it.  A really few really nice combos I discovered while play-testing.  You can summon 'Silent Wobby' to your opponents side of the field, and not only do you gain 2000 life-points, wobby also acts as fodder to start that kaiju brawl.  if you start with 'Owner's Seal in your hand, you can instead of Special Summoning two kaijus, summon 1 to your opponent's side of the field then retake control of it leaving your opponent theoretically defenseless.  In the current META due to 20 minute long combos that involve lots of tributing and discarding and effect activating getting 'Kyoutou Waterfront' out on the field is essential!  'Neo-Spacian Grand Mole' can make a pretty nifty loop combo, by tributing your opponents boss monster to summon a kaiju before sp. summoining your own and normal summoning 'Grand Mole', you can attack your opponent's kaiju with 'Grand Mole' and send it back to your hand leaving them without a boss monster, you can continue this loop almost infinitely.  KUMONGOUS. IS. IMPORTANT. negating your opponent's ability to activate effects and attack in this current META is the best thing you can do, it can and will cancel their combo's leaving them wide open. if you find yourself against an overly effect reliant deck such as sky-strikers, time lords or subterrors Kumongous can throw off their entrie strategy, and paired with Kyoutou Waterfront, is really self sustainable.  Be mindful when summoning Gameciel to your opponents side of the field. Yes, he is the weakest Kaiju monster stat wise but thats a balancing chip with him. If there are readily accesible kaiju counters while once you've summoned Gameicel its better to take him out first before going for any potentially game ending effects (like Dogoran's).

deck_excerpt: Most consistent "meta" build for Winged Dragon of Ra
deck_description:
So you wanna devote yourself to the Sun itself? This is the most consistent build you will find. Once more i searched the web trying to find a good decklist for this deck, i didn't find the perfect one, so i had to make one myself. Servants of the Sun:
  • Before you summon your Egyptian God you need to summon his pawns, for that you have Sangan, the starter of the Deck, if you don't open your hand with him don't worry, Tour Guide Of The Underworld searches it for you.
  • When you dump Sangan for a Link Summon be it Almiraj or Masquerena you will search for Arboria, your extender. Then you will make the most boring combo nowadays and abuse Halqifibrax.
  • Arboria Special Summons itself from your hand, so you Link into Halqi, Summon O-Lion from your deck, Link Halqi into Linkross, Synchro Summon the Level 3 Metal Marcher and Special Summon Arboria from the GY.
  • With the Token summoned by O-Lion, you go into Union Carrier, target Arboria in your field and equip Guardian Slime to her, there's still one Level 1 Token left, so you Synchro Summon Hastorr for maximum ATK Points and Monster Steal or Arc Light for the negate, thus dumping Guardian Slime and enabling you to search any card that supports Ra.
  • You can also use Crystal Girl, to search for Guardian Slime. One for One facilitates that.
  • Temple of the Kings allows you to activate Metal Reflect Slime in the same turn it is set, so you can summon Ra more easily.
Bringing the Sun to the battlefield:
  • Now that the offerings are in your field, you can use them as tributes for the Sun God, there are a lot of scenarios that can happen, the most common one is that you search Ancient Chant with the Guardian Slime you just dumped, bring Ra to your hand and summon him.
  • If you go first you will want to summon Sphere Mode before bringing Ra to the field so you don't spend your LP.
  • If you already have Ancient Chant in your hand you can go for Millenium Revelation, so you can search for Monster Reborn if needed or even One With The Sun God so if anything happens to Ra, you gain your LP back.
Become one with the flames and bear the name of Phoenix:
  • You also cannot forget that you have Immortal Phoenix in your deck, and there are a two ways of sending it to the GY. One of them and the best one is Millenium Revelation, discard Phoenix and search Monster Reborn.
  • You can also discard it for the effect of One for One in order to summon Crystal Girl.
  • When you have it there your GY is set up as well. If Ra goes to the GY by any means, Immortal Phoenix rises from its ashes and allows you to destroy your opponent's field. One With The Sun God allows you to do that
  Some extra explanations:
  • Instant Fusion allows you to bring Theseus a tuner to the field, so you can make Halqifibrax most of the time.
  • Mound of the Bound Creator offers extra protection to your Winged Dragon of Ra.
  • Life Absorbing Machine can be replaced.
  • Don't forget Blaze Cannon you can search it with Guardian Slime and it can decide the duel.
  Any suggestions or questions leave it down below. Also you can check my profile in Dueling Book, it's _Theseus. Now burn your opponent with the Sun itself, and make sure they become a Sun God devotee as well!

deck_excerpt: A going first Hero Deck for the June 2020 format (created before June Banlist)
deck_description:
Step by Step Tutorial for a Basic Hero Combo:   Hand: Vision HERO Faris, Solemn Judgment, Mask Change, Evil HERO Adusted Gold, Elemental HERO Shadow Mist  
  1. Special Summon Faris by discarding Shadow Mist (don't activate Shadow Mists effect just yet)
  2. Place Vision HERO Increase from your Deck in your Spell/Trap Zone.
  3. Summon Increase by putting Faris in the GY.
  4. Special Summon Vision HERO Vyon from your Deck and activate his effect to mill Destiny HERO - Malicious
  5. Special Summon a new Malicious with his effect from Deck by banishing him from the GY.
  6. Link Malicious and Increase to Xtra HERO - Cross Crusader and Special Summon Malicious from Grave by his effect.
  7. Use Cross Crusaders Effect to send Malicious to the GY and get Elemental HERO Liquid Soldier in your Hand
  8. Normal Summon Liquid Soldier and revive Shadow Mist to get another Mask Change into your Hand
  9. Use Mask Change on Shadow Mist to summon Dark Law
  10. Activate Evil HERO Adusted Golds effect to get Dark Calling.
  11. Activate Dark Calling by banishing Adusted Gold and Faris to summon Evil HERO Malicious Edge
  12. Activate Mask Change to Summon Masked HERO Acid
  13. Set down Solemn Judgment and attack or pass depending on the game state/turn.

deck_excerpt: Watch your opponent fail this raid and cyberse him away.
deck_description: So the Main 1-card-combo here is to use Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight send World Legacy - "World Armor" to GY. Use Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight effect to summon tokens, link one token to Linkuriboh, now link for Lib the World Key Blademaster, use her effect to set World Legacy Succession. Use World Legacy Succession to bring back World Legacy - "World Armor", search for World Legacy Monstrosity. Link Lib to Linkross and summon the tokens. Use one token to revive Linkuriboh. Fusion/special summon Trishula, the Dragon of Icy Imprisonment, activate World Legacy Monstrosity to summon Harr, Generaider Boss of Storms and Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light. Fetch Generaider Boss Stage with Mardel (if needed). Xyz Mardel and Trishula to Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. Activate the Boss Stage. Use Jormungandr effect, attach your Linkross and chain Harr. Boss Stages triggers and brings a next Generaider to Xyz Rank 9 again for True King of All Calamities. Hand neutral combo and you now have 2 Rank 9s and your Boss Stage. As soon as you see an opening in their board you can go for OTK. That is why the cyberse/salamangreat cards are here for. You just need to link climb to either I:P Masquerena or Update Jammer then go into Transcode Talker, use his effect bring back that used link monster, link summon Accesscode Talker with 5k+ atk and a second attack during this turn if summoned with update jammer. Additional to that he can pop at least 2 cards and this effect cant be negated. Easiest way to reach your needed Link-2 is with formud skipper, link to Salamangreat Balelynx, use his effect and get Salamangreat Sanctuary into your hand and search your parallel exceed. Activate the sanctuary, link summon your second Salamangreat Balelynx, SS your parallel exceed, use the effect and summon one more parallel exceed from your deck. link them to update jammer. link jammer and Balelynx to Transcode talker. Use his effect bring back update jammer, link summon accesscode talker, use his effect and select Transcode talker and chain update jammer effect.

deck_excerpt: This Tindangle deck isn't exactly Meta, but can still pull off loads of wombo-combos if set-up correctly. If anything goes wrong like effects get nega
deck_description: To start a good 1st turn combo if you have a foolish burial, you have a good start, so foolish a Tindangle Intruder, then trigger Tindangle Jhrelth to discard any Tindangle's in your hand and deck(Discard a Tindangle Protector or DHoles.) to special SET it. Next you use DHoles ability to revive the other Tindangle(NOT Intruder or DHoles), then Intruder will chain the effect and will special summon itself in face down position. You should have 3 face down monsters. Then you activate Nagel's Protection to make your Tindangles's invincible to your opponents card effects.Finally End your Turn. When your opponents monster attacks the Tindangle, make sure they attack the Jhrelth or Intruderr to flip them face up and add 2 Tindangle monster's from your deck to your hand. FYI Your opponent can flip Protecter to trigger its search effect that will flip all the Tindangle's and search even more cards.(About 3 if used correctly.) Then you want to activate your searched Jhrelth to discard the TRAP Tindangle Delaunay to then activate Delaunay's effect to banish itself  to summon back the destroyed Tindangle's last turn. But if they negated it, don't worry, just stall out for one turn. Use Trinity since he is immune to battle. Then activate the Tindangle Delaunay that was previously negated(If it wasn't just LINK Summon Tindangle Acute Cerberus just make sure to put Tindangle Base Gardna in the GY.) to summon DHoles, Jhrelth, Protector and Intruder. Wait for your opponent to do their turn. When they're done, you want to flip Protector face up to reveal the rest of the Tindangle's to draw 3 cards. Next, activate Jhrelth's effect to search any Tindangle. After That, you can LINK Summon Acute Cerberus. If you use Trinity as one of the materials you can search a Gergonne's End and discard a Euler's Circuit to the GY, then activate Euler's Circuit to banish itself and discard 1 Tindangle in your hand to serach another Euler's Circuit and then activate the field spell to make it where your opponent cannot attack you if you control 3 or more Tindangle monsters which you probably already have with a lot of set-up.(Also you should activate a Nagel's Protection along with the wombo-combo you did to put a lot of Tindangle's in the GY especially Base Gardna.)When you activate Nagel and you attack with Acute Cerberus doing double damage and could OTK if u have 2 Tindangle's CO-LINKED to Acute Ceberus. Although it seems like a tough deck to set-up since this is a flip deck. You can actually pull off some NEAT Wombo-Combo's. Eldlich Zombies deck. The goal is to be a Zombies deck, running Eldlich cards as a control engine. It means running 2 card combos instead of Jet Synchron, and makes the routing a little heavy on extra deck space, but the deck has follow-up and interactions for days. Let's begin. 3 Uni-Zombie and 2 Shiranui Solitaire make up an eighth of the deck, meaning odds are we'll see them in our top 8 cards. These numbers are run because with 6 it always feels like you see 2 too often. These form a 2 card combo with any of Zombie World, Glow-Up Bloom, or Necroworld Banshee. 2 Banshee and 2 Glow-Up Bloom give us access to Zombie world in the case of banshee, and the choice of Doomking Balerdroch or Eldlich the Golden Lord from Glow-Up Bloom. These numbers help ensure you see the combo reasonably often, and makes follow-up plays possible. 2 Doomking Balerdroch are the maindeck boss monsters, and make a Halquifibrax combo that ends on 3 interactions plus Zombie World. Vampire Fraulein is an OTK with Dragonecro, in addition to being a level 5 combo piece and defensive hand trap. Worth it as a 1 of in the Zombie build, because you can summon it with Eldlixers, and pure Zombies plays it anyways. Rivalry of Warlords locks people out of playing non-zombie monsters with Zombie World, and is basically a Zombie card. Super Poly is likewise a zombie card, and is a 1 of to search it with Predaplant Verte Anaconda to make Dragonecro super poly as a link 2, just a 3rd line of play that's good going second, basically. 3 Zombie World is essential, half of our deck only works if this card is on the field, so playing 3 with everyone running Cosmic Cyclone for Eldlich seems like a good idea. For the Eldlich half of the deck, we have pretty standard numbers with some minor trims for deckspace reasons. 3 Golden Lord is pretty standard. Zombies plays 2 of these anyways, and we need to have more Golden Lords than we do Eldlich cards in a game. They're gonna get banished so 3 is essential in my opinion. 3 Cursed Eldland is insane, if find you Golden Lord, it finds you other interaction, it sets up your GY, this card is also nuts with Performapal Popperup going first. It's also one of the Eldlich combo extenders needed for second string follow-ups / alternatives. 3 Scarlet Sanguine, but only 2 Black Awakening and 1 White Destiny. Different names are important, as is recuring zombie threats such as golden lord and Balerdroch. These 6 cards are all also extenders in second string plays. 2 each of Conquistador and Huaquero is pretty standard, these are the meat of the deck, and combo pieces. 1 Golden Land Forever gives us a searchable omni-negate, good in games when you just go off on turn one, and pretty okay in middling games as well. I'd run 2, but space is tight. 3 Performapal Popperup is our card draw of choice. I know it works well in Eldlich, and it definitely has synergies in Zombies. Drawing 3 cards deeper into the deck while pitching cards for fun and profit leads to some extreme highs, and it can mitigate middling hands as a mulligan in a pinch. Better than Souls' here because we want to pitch monsters about as often as spells/traps. Mecha Phantom Beast O-Lion is a brick, but it makes the Herald+Raptite combo possible. Ghost Ogre is not a complete brick, but it here to be an extra interruption off of Needlefibre. Easy money. We even make the Ghost Girl a ghost with Zombie World. Extra deck space is tight. 3 Needlefibre are essential. 2 are used in the deck's main combo, and 1 is used in follow-up plays. Linkuriboh makes Glow-Up Bloom into full combo with Zombie World, which just increases the odds of seeing 2 card Needlefibre combos more often. Linkross, Martial Metalmarcher, and Wonder Magician go into Borreload Savage on your opponent's turn + Herald of the Arc Light on yours, plus maybe a spell/trap pop with Wonder Magician out of our 2 card Needlefibres. The second engine is a 3 card combo, but a fairly redundant one to put together, which ends on Ghost Ogre + Huquero/Conquistador interruption + Dawn Dragster on their turn, which draws a card off Formula Synchron. You can even use Fraulein for added consistency. The last string of plays is Predaplant Verte Anaconda to Super Poly their monsters into Dragonecro. I'd love to run more of these, but space is sooo tight in the main and extra. Train cards eventually win games by OTKs. Red Splatter makes this much easier. Combo 1 can be done with a bunch of cards, but for simplicity, we'll focus on Uni-Zombie + Zombie World.
  1. Play Zombie World
  2. Play Uni-Zombie
  3. Send Glow-Up Bloom to GY
  4. Banish Bloom, ss Balerdroch
  5. Link Balerdroch and Uni-Zombie into Needlefibre, ss O-Lion.
  6. Link Needlefibre in Linkross, ss 2 tokens.
  7. Synchro O-Lion and a token into Martial Metalmarcher. O-lion chain 2, Marcher chain 1, ss token, ss Uni-Zombie.
  8. Synchro Marcher + level 3 token into Raptite with O-lion in the GY. Synchro Herald of the Arclight.
  9. During opponents standby phase ss Balerdroch.
Zombie World locks you out of Auroradon. Combo 2 involves previously mentioned Zombie cards plus a bunch of combinations of Eldlich cards. For simplicity, we'll use Uni-Zombie, Zombie World, and Red Splatter.
  1. Play Zombie World
  2. Normal Summon Uni-Zombie. Send Glow-Up Bloom to the GY.
  3. Banish Glow-Up Bloom, ss Golden Lord.
  4. Link Uni-Zombie and Golden Lord into Needlefibre, ss Ghost Ogre.
  5. Set Red Eldlixir.
  6. ss Golden Lord, send red splatter to the GY.
  7. Banish Red Eldlixir for your choice of Conquistador and Huaquero.
  8. Opponents turn you have Ghost Ogre, an Eldlich Trap, and you can banish Needlefibre to ss Formula Synchron, draw a card, and synchro it and the level 5 monster into Dawn Dragster for a negate.
The third-string play is just Super Poly out of Verte Anaconda, a power play for sure and great going second to break boards. Profile already changed. Basically I'm trying to make the grind game more consistent.

deck_excerpt: Bait out hand traps with gallant and doki then go for halq combo and make an oppressive board.
deck_description: Your primary goal with this deck is to try and turbo out Halqifibrax after your opponent has used their hand trap and before you Normal Summon. Ideally you need to go first, this deck will struggle vs an established board. If you can make Gallant Granite before Halq, do it and the opponent will be forced to negate it. Gallant and Doki are cards the opponent are forced to negate otherwise they'll give you too much advantage. If you can resolve Halq then go for Martial Metal Marcher combos and it should be off to the races. You're playing 4 copies of Block Dragon, try and hold it as long as possible or use it as material for an Apollousa. Block Dragon is how you're pushing through hand traps, without Block Dragon you're likely to lose. Worst case scenario, you can attach it using Union Carrier but you more want to save Carrier to attach Buster Dragon to force the opponent to scoop. The ideal end board should comprise of: Apollousa of at least 3 negates, Union Carrier, I:P Masquerena, Herald of the Arc Light, Savage Dragon with 2 counters and Buster Dragon attached, Dweller with Tackle Crusader as material, and Block Dragon to be used with I:P to make unicorn which will then be co-linked with Carrier to go +4.     Game 2 Side in the hand traps and try to block the opponent's combo as best you can. You have 14 hand traps to work with, all of which can either block Halq Combos or stop Auroradon/Linkross combos, so use them wisely. Game 3 side in exchange to get rid of dark ruler or anything else that can threaten your board. Toughest matchup is the mirror since its very die roll dependent. Its not impossible to win going second vs the mirror but its quite an uphill battle if you dont open imperm or nibiru.

deck_excerpt: Brotherhood of the Fire Fist deck with Lightsworn engine
deck_description: Pure Fire Fist in my opinion was a bit too bricky so I tried to find a good engine for them. The best I could come up with was Lightsworns since they have couple of Beast-Warriors to go for Eagle and use as material for Swan. They can also mill cards to grave which helps with Eagle's, Panda's and Dragon's effects. The spells can also mill Wulf which makes summoning arguably the most improtant card of the deck, Eagle, easier. I first tried using Luminas instead of Aurkus, Lightsworn Monk but kept constantly wanting Lumina to be a Beast-Warrior type so I changed it. I think adding the Lightsworns made the deck brick less and make better combos but it is still quite bricky and starting the combos needs a bit too much resources compared to some meta decks for example. Hence the lack of hand traps and other generic protection and destruction cards. Replays: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lLuc22l4xps

deck_excerpt: Pre Toon Chaos but who have thought Toon is a Halq engine by itself and the endboard with Herald of the Arc Light sets the follow up with Relinquished
deck_description: Toon is very similar to Malefic, because its just a new approach to already existing popular cards, but it allows us to run those popular cards support to fetch the Toons, making it more consistent and has more tools. The combo is we make 2 lv7 on field and overlay it to Ebon Illusion Magician to fetch our tuner Magicalibra for Halqifibrax combo. Toon Dark Magician and Toon Red-Eyes Black Dragon easily accompolish that, so we play to turbo both. Cards like The Black Stone of Legend (our main normal summon, ss Red-Eyes from deck), Magicians Souls (fetches Toon DM to gy or ss og DM as lv7 fodder), Toon Table of Contents (adds any Toon, mostly Toon DM as Toon Red-Eyes can summon it from hand), Where Arf Thou (works with both Black Stone and Magicians Souls), One for One, Dark Magic Veil (ss dark spellcaster from hand or gy, works with DM lineup), and lastly Tenyi Adhara (tuner lv1) or Vishuda (lv7 with bounce effect). The Halqifibrax combo with Borreload Savage Dragon and Herald of the Arc Light is very suitable to this deck as it only uses small extra deck space and can search Relinquished lineup as follow up play. Fusion lineup is for either Eyes Restrict or Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon (since we run og DM, I think Dragoon is the best addition here), being Instant Fusion and Magicalized Fusion (Millenium-Eyes Restrict or Dragoon). Not only that, Dark Magic Veil can revive both Eyes Restrict and Dragoon too. We also use spellcaster support like Selene for Accescode since the Toon spell easily dump 3 spells and we run bunch of spellcaster anyway. Can put in Chimeratech Megafleet too as we have Toon Cyber Dragon. Toon Briefcase is just another search target and we can make it online if we have Toon monster for spare. Kaiju works well too, either as Relinquished fodder or lv7 xyz material. Imduk is there to utilize og DM with Magicalized Fusion for Dragoon. We dont play the Toon Kingdom lineup as it banishes 3 cards from deck (we have combo pieces) and while its protection effect is good, sitting on Toon monsters aint good enough. Relinquished also clashes with Toon as Relinquished is super good going second while most of the Toons cant atk the turn they are summoned, so this deck is made to synergize both Relinquished and Toon. Pros: Themed, good board setup with follow up, consistency is borderline acceptable. Cons: Board is easily broken, lack of recursion, both Toon DM and Red-Eyes cant atk the turn it is summoned and only have moderate atk as beater.

Resuce Rabbit and use its effect to summon two gem-knights from deck.  3.Link 1 Gem-knight into a link spider then use link spider effect to special the last gem-knight in your hand.  4.Use the two gem-knights a go into phantom quartz use its effect to search gem-knight fusion, and then use its second effect shuffling 3 gem-knights back to deck to summon lady brilliant diamond.  5.Use her effect to tribute phantom quartz to summon seraphinite.  6.Then summon Curious, using its effect send block dragon.  7.Use block dragon to banish 3 and summon it to the field (try to keep as many gem-knight normal monsters in grave)  8.Link Block Dragon and Curious into Apollusa and use its effect searching gem-knight obsidian,lapis and crystal rose.  9.use obsidian, lapis and fuse them into lapis lazuli using gem-knight fusion, use obsidian to summon lapis back.  10.turn lapis into a link spider (just to send it to grave)  11.use lapis lazuli effect to send a lazuli from deck to grave to add lapis back to hand.  12.Use Gem-Knight fusion from grave to banish a gem-knight to add it back to hand.  13.Use it to summon seraphinite using lapis and crystal rose( due note if u have invoker in hand u havent use seraphinite effect to normal summon so u can actually normal summon it for invocation to skip the need of madness)  14.use crystal rose to banish lady brilliant to summon itself to the deck_description: Cyberse (サイバース Saibāsu) is a Type of monster. This Type is used by Yusaku Fujiki, Varis, Bohman, BitBoot, Takeru Homura, Earth, Windy, Lightning, Haru, Skye Zaizen, Ai, and Pandorin Yu-Gi-Oh! VRAINS. Appearance-wise, they resemble creatures and humanoids strongly connected to elements of digital technology and cyberspace. At times though, they tend to resemble either Insect, Machineor Psychic monsters (the humanoids bearing design elements from the TRONfranchise). The name is a portmanteau of "Cyber" (サイバー Saibā) and "Universe" (ユニバース Yunibāsu).  Their general theme revolves around swarming the field with weak monsters to easily Link Summon powerful Link Monsters, and they also have lots of monsters that gain effects when banished in a similar vein to Psychic monsters.
